0and%20professionalism.%20Hendriksen%20agreed%20that%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bskills%20deficit%26quot%3B%20for%20Gen%20Zers%20in%20the%20customer%20service%20and%20retail%20space%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20said%20that%20the%20group%20isn't%20a%20monolith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20normal%20for%20norms%20around%20professionalism%20and%20etiquette%20to%20shift%2C%20Gerhardt%20said%2C%20but%20it's%20more%20productive%20to%20work%20with%20young%20people%20on%20striking%20the%20right%20tone%20than%20to%20try%20to%20mock%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20don't%20lose%20this%20personal%20touch%2C%20then%20let's%20meet%20them%20where%20they're%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20invest%20in%20helping%20them%20understand%20why%20that's%20important%20and%20see%20what%20they%20need%20to%20get%20where%20their%20bosses%20or%20customers%20feel%20like%20they%20need%20to%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22df035915-9034-4926-b956-56e386c7b194%5C%22%3EGenerational%20critique%20isn't%20anything%20new%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20any%20new%20generation%20has%20entered%20the%20workforce%2C%20they've%20needed%20to%20get%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20a%20set%20of%20skills%2C%20said%20Gerhardt.%20The%20viral%20criticism%20of%20the%20so-called%20Gen%20Z%20Stare%20reminds%20her%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-social-media-habits-tiktok-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emillennial%20pause%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20phenomenon%20and%20feels%20like%20the%20%26quot%3Blatest%20iteration%20of%20generational%20shaming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20no%20dearth%20of%20criticism%20targeting%20various%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20that%20boomers%20are%20selfish%2C%20or%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmany-millennials-dont-see-themselves-as-mille