22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68769a383d5881a51c1d5f48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225402%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%208th%20Circuit%20blocked%20the%20FTC's%20rule%20that%20would've%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20cancel%20subscriptions.%3Cp%3ESolStock%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%208th%20Circuit%20blocked%20the%20FTC's%20%26quot%3Bclick-to-cancel%26quot%3B%20rule%20over%20claims%20of%20procedural%20issues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20rule%20would%20have%20made%20it%20as%20easy%20for%20a%20consumer%20to%20cancel%20a%20subscription%20as%20it%20was%20to%20sign%20up.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20the%20provision%20is%20blocked%2C%20there%20are%20ongoing%20state%20and%20congressional%20efforts%20to%20ease%20subscription%20traps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancel-subscriptions-easier-flight-refunds-customer-service-gym-memberships-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClick-to-cancel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20were%20just%20days%20away%20from%20accessing%20an%20easy%20exit%20route%20from%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esubscription%20traps%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20On%20July%2014%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission's%20rule%20to%20make%20subscriptions%20as%20easy%20to%20cancel%20as%20they%20were%20to%20sign%20up%2C%20commonly%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bclick-to-cancel%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%208th%20Circuit%20threw%20a%20wrench%20in%20those%20plans%20in%20a%20July%208%20ruling%20that%20blocked%20the%20FTC's%20click-to-cancel%20provisions.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20the%20commission%20failed%20to%20follow%20proper%20procedure%20when%20soliciting%20feedback%20on%20its%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20certainly%20do%20not%20endorse%20the%20use%20of%20unfair%20and%20deceptive%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ruling%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20procedural%20deficiencies%20of%20the%20Commission's%20rulemaking%20process%20are%20fatal%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeale%20Mahoney%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20most%20direct%20impact%20of%20the%208th%20Circuit's%20ruling%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20just%20going%20to%20waste%20people's%20time%20rather%20than%20being%20able%20to%20cancel%20easily.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20block%20out%20time%20during%20work%20and%20sit%20on%20hold%2C%20or%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20navigate%20frustrating%20cancellation%20flows%20on%20company%20websites%2C%26quot%3B%20Mahoney%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20I%20think%20people%20have%20difficult%20everyday%20lives%2C%20and%20this%20just%20adds%20to%20the%20annoyances%20of%20people%20being%20able%20to%20make%20the%20decisions%20they%20want%20as%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20become%20increasingly%20adept%20at%20holding%20consumers%20in%20subscription%20plans%20using%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20interpret%20a%20consumer's%20silence%20as%20an%20agreement%20to%20continue%20purchasing%20a%20product%2C%20rather%20than%20requiring%20customers%20to%20actively%20agree%20to%20recurring%20charges.%20This%20is%20why%20you%20might%20find%20yourself%20looking%20at%20your%20credit%20card%20bill%20one%20month%2C%20trying%20to%20decipher%20a%20list%20of%20charges%20you%20don't%20remember%20signing%20up%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20FTC%20has%20had%20a%20rule%20in%20place%20regulating%20negative%20options%20for%20decades%2C%20the%20click-to-cancel%20provision%20was%20the%20most%20recent%20amendment%20to%20change%20the%20way%20subscriptions%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELina%20Khan%2C%20the%20FTC's%20commissioner%20under%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20who%20led%20the%20subscription%20rule%2C%20pushed%20back%20on%20the%208th%20Circuit's%20claims.%20She%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Flinamkhan%2Fstatus%2F1943346583153905733%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20that%20the%20rulemaking%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bprocess%20that%20took%203%2B%20years%20and%20required%20reviewing%2016k%20comments%20%26amp%3B%20giving%20industry%20a%20chance%20to%20present%20their%20views%20at%20an%20FTC%20hearing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20consumers%2C%20the%20ruling%20means%20spending%20more%20time%20and%20money%20navigating%20the%20subscription%20cancellation%20bureaucracy.%20The%20impacts%20on%20the%20economy%20are%20broader%20%E2%80%94%20Mahoney%20said%20that%20since%20subscription%20traps%20lock%20people%20into%20products%20and%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20switch%2C%20they'll%20decrease%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20when%20markets%20are%20less%20competitive%2C%20then%20firms%20have%20less%20incentive%20to%20lower%20their%20prices%2C%20they%20have%20less%20incentive%20to%20improve%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20Mahoney%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20fundamentally%20see%20this%20as%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20annoying%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20waste%20people's%20time%2C%20but%20more%20broadly%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20lessen%20the%20forces%20of%20competition%20and%20lead%20to%20higher%20prices%20and%20lower%20quality%20in%20subscription%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%208th%20Circuit's%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8ec50d0-f5ef-428d-a150-eff26e154324%5C%22%3EWhere%20subscriptions%20go%20from%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%208th%20Circuit's%20block%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20click-to-cancel%20is%20gone.%20The%20FTC%20could%20choose%20to%20appeal%20the%20ruling%3B%20Erin%20Witte%2C%20director%20of%20consumer%20protection%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20was%20surprised%20to%20see%20%26quot%3Bhow%20vigorously%26quot%3B%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20FTC%20defended%20the%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20FTC%20filed%20a%20brief%20in%20March%20supporting%20the%20negative%20option%20and%20click-to-cancel%20rule%2C%20writing%20that%20consumers%20%26quot%3Bface%20unnecessary%20obstacles%20from%20sellers%20who%20force%20them%20to%20endure%20multiple%20phone%20calls%2C%20long%20hold%20times%2C%20and%20countless%20automated%20menus.%20Studies%20show%20that%20most%20Americans%20pay%20hundreds%20annually%20for%20unwanted%20subscriptions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFTC's%20commissioner%20Mark%20Meador%20took%20a%20different%20tone%20last%20week%20when%20he%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMeadorFTC%2Fstatus%2F1942682515480928423%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20following%20the%208th%20Circuit's%20ruling%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20FTC's%20click-to-cancel%20rule%2C%20which%20would%20have%20made%20it%20much%20easier%20for%20consumers%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20unwanted%20online%20subscriptions%2C%20isn't%20going%20into%20effect%20for%20one%20reason%3A%20the%20Biden%20FTC%20cut%20corners%20and%20didn't%20follow%20the%20law.%20Process%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20the%20FTC%20likely%20won't%20appeal%20the%20ruling%2C%20Witte%20said%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20are%20existing%20state%20regulations%20and%20congressional%20efforts%20to%20ease%20the%20subscription%20cancellation%20process.%20John%20Breyault%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20public%20policy%20for%20telecommunications%20and%20fraud%20at%20the%20National%20Consumers%20League%2C%20referenced%20California's%20click-to-cancel%20rule%20that%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20signed%20into%20law%20last%20year%2C%20requiring%20businesses%20in%20the%20state%20to%20make%20subscriptions%20as%20easy%20to%20cancel%20as%20they%20were%20to%20opt%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20Sen.%20Brian%20Schatz%20and%20Republican%20Sen.%20John%20Kennedy%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.schatz.senate.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Ffollowing-court-ruling-blocking-click-to-cancel-rule-schatz-kennedy-introduce-legislation-to-stop-deceptive-subscription-business-practices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Unsubscribe%20Act%20on%20July%2010.%20The%20act%20would%20require%20companies%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%20about%20their%20subscription%20models%20and%20make%20them%20easy%20to%20cancel.%20It%20would%20also%20require%20companies%20to%20periodically%20notify%20consumers%20of%20their%20subscription%20and%20how%20they%20can%20cancel%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229fc85bad-0240-4f47-84ea-3a12e523f4ed%5C%22%3EWhat%20subscription%20rules%20mean%20for%20businesses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESubscriptions%20are%20advantageous%20to%20businesses%20because%20they%20can%20rely%20on%20that%20recurring%20revenue%2C%20but%20making%20them%20easy%20to%20cancel%20%26quot%3Bseems%20like%20a%20pretty%20low%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Teresa%20Murray%2C%20who%20oversees%20consumer%20issues%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20Public%20Interest%20Research%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20company%2C%20why%20would%20you%20want%20to%20have%20customers%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20your%20customers%3F%20Why%20would%20you%20want%20to%20take%20money%20from%20people%20who%20are%20making%20a%20good-faith%20effort%20to%20cancel%3F%20That%20just%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20a%20good%20business%20model%2C%26quot%3B%20Murray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%2C%20however%2C%20that%20consumers%20should%20also%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20ensuring%20they%20comply%20with%20their%20signed-up%20terms%2C%20such%20as%20setting%20calendar%20reminders%20to%20cancel%20free%20trials%20and%20keeping%20copies%20of%20email%20confirmations%20detailing%20the%20subscription%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreyault%20said%20that%20even%20with%20the%208th%20Circuit's%20block%2C%20some%20companies%20may%20have%20already%20started%20rethinking%20their%20subscription%20models%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20unlikely%20anything%20will%20change%20wide%20scale%20absent%20a%20federal%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20what%20you'll%20see%20is%20that%20companies%20will%20start%20looking%20at%20how%20they're%20marketing%20these%20subscriptions%2C%20how%20easy%20or%20difficult%20it%20is%20for%20consumers%20to%20cancel%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Breyault%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that%20some%20of%20them%20may%20take%20action%20voluntarily%20to%20reform%20how%20they%20do%20this%2C%20but%20without%20the%20rule%20in%20place%2C%20companies%20that%20profit%20off%20of%20offering%20them%20deceptively%20are%20likely%20to%20continue%20to%20do%20so%20in%20a%20way%20that%20harms%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-blocks-subscription-trap-click-to-cancel-ftc-rule-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752692723000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68769a8f3d5881a51c1d5f53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-blocks-subscription-trap-click-to-cancel-ftc-rule-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20FTC's%20rule%20to%20make%20canceling%20subscriptions%20as%20easy%20as%20they%20were%20to%20sign%20up%20was%20blocked%20just%20days%20before%20it%20was%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-blocks-subscription-trap-click-to-cancel-ftc-rule-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LISTEN%3A%20Netflix%20Q2%20Earnings%20Preview%3