ps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6876921385e81483682e0cae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221824%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20internal%20drivers%20are%20powerful%2C%20and%20we%20love%20the%20headphones'%20tactile%20buttons%20and%20physical%20power%20switch.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Hayes%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nothing%20Headphone%20(1)%20aren't%20just%20about%20appearances.%20They%20also%20have%20functional%20design%20touches%20that%20work%20well.%20The%20controls%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20excellent.%20There's%20a%20volume%20roller%20and%20track%20rocker%20on%20the%20right%20ear%20cup.%20You%20slide%20your%20finger%20left%20and%20right%20over%20the%20roller%20to%20change%20the%20volume.%20It%20feels%20great%2C%20really%20natural%2C%20and%20tactile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20do%20wonder%20why%20the%20direction%20wasn't%20up%20and%20down%20on%20the%20roller%20instead.%20The%20rocker%20paddle%20underneath%20the%20roller%20is%20easy%20to%20feel%20for%20and%20tap%20left%20or%20right.%20Supposedly%2C%20holding%20it%20down%20in%20either%20direction%20will%20activate%20fast%20forward%20or%20reverse%20scrubbing%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20get%20that%20to%20work%20with%20an%20iPhone%20using%20Apple%20Music%20or%20Spotify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20great%20as%20those%20intuitive%20media%20controls%20are%2C%20my%20favorite%20design%20touch%20is%20actually%20the%20headphones'%20physical%20switch%20for%20power.%20It's%20a%20tiny%20detail%20but%20critical%20to%20everyday%20use.%20Nearly%20all%20headphones%20nowadays%20use%20a%20button%20for%20power%2C%20and%20depending%20on%20how%20long%20you%20press%20it%2C%20this%20same%20button%20is%20often%20used%20to%20activate%20Bluetooth%20pairing.%20As%20such%2C%20I'm%20never%20sure%20how%20long%20to%20hold%20a%20button%20to%20turn%20a%20pair%20of%20headphones%20on%20and%20off.%20This%20switch%20eliminates%20that%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20round%20out%20the%20controls%2C%20there's%20an%20extra%20button%20on%20the%20exterior%20right%20cup%2C%20open%20to%20be%20customized.%20It's%20set%20to%20activate%20your%20voice%20assistant%20by%20default%2C%20but%20using%20the%20Nothing%20X%20app%20allows%20you%20to%20change%20it.%20I%20made%20it%20the%20ANC%20toggle%20and%20found%20that%20to%20be%20perfect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222432%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20angled%20view%20of%20the%20Nothing%20Headphone%20(1)%20case%20resting%20on%20a%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687692503d5881a51c1d5e08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221824%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20one%20major%20weak%20point%20in%20the%20package%20is%20the%20headphones'%20case%2C%20which%20is%20lackluster.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Hayes%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20hood%2C%20the%20Headphone%20(1)%20feature%2040mm%20dynamic%20drivers%20with%20a%20frequency%20range%20of%2020Hz-40KHz%2C%20and%20they%20support%20AAC%2C%20SBC%2C%20and%20LDAC%20audio%20codecs.%20Six%20microphones%20are%20built-in%20to%20enable%20real-time%20adaptive%20ANC%2C%20four%20of%20which%20are%20used%20for%20voice%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20battery%20life%20is%20listed%20at%2035%20hours%20with%20ANC%20on%20or%2080%20hours%20with%20it%20off.%20You%20can%20ignore%20the%2080-hour%20number%20as%20you'll%20only%20want%20to%20use%20these%20with%20ANC%20or%20transparency%20enabled.%20Once%20the%20battery%20dies%2C%20they%20charge%20quickly%20in%20120%20minutes%2C%20as%20advertised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20weigh%20329%20grams%20but%20feel%20lighter%20in%20practice.%20They%20also%20have%20multi-device%20support%2C%20on-ear%20detection%2C%20and%20an%20IP52%20water%20and%20dust%20rating.%20The%20latter%20should%20make%20them%20safe%20for%20commuting%20during%20inclement%20weather%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20suitable%20for%20use%20with%20dripping%20sweat%20while%20at%20the%20gym.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20that%20these%20headphones%20support%20listening%20via%20Bluetooth%2C%20a%203.5mm%20cable%2C%20or%20USB-C%20audio.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20wireless%20will%20be%20sufficient%2C%20but%20having%20extra%20options%20is%20always%20nice.%20That%20said%2C%20they%20still%20require%20power%20when%20using%20a%20wired%20connection%2C%20which%20is%20a%20bummer%20if%20you%20want%20to%20listen%20with%20a%20cable%20as%20a%20backup%20when%20the%20battery%20has%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20one%20reason%20to%20be%20mad%20at%20these%20headphones%2C%20look%20no%20further%20than%20the%20case.%20It's%20woolly%2C%20scratchy%2C%20and%20just%20kind%20of%20sucks.%20Touching%20it%20nearly%20makes%20my%20skin%20crawl.%20The%20Headphone%20(1)%20case%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fsonos-ace-headphones-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESonos%20Ace%3C%2Fa%3E%20case.%20I%20don't%20like%20either%20of%20those%20cases%20because%20of%20the%20texture.%20The%20zipper%20isn't%20smooth%20to%20open%20or%20close%20either.%20More%20companies%20should%20look%20into%20magnetic%20closures%20and%20copy%20what%20Sony%20did%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fsony-wh-1000xm6-headphones-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWH-1000XM6%3C%2Fa%3E%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a92f7584-e50f-442b-88a6-24096bb73ef3%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Audio%20quality%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAudio%20quality%20is%20mostly%20neutral%2C%20but%20bass%20lovers%20won't%20be%20left%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221721%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Nothing%20Headphone%20(1)%20lying%20on%20a%20dresser.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687692a3f748d8c055f5a6a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221291%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Headphone%20(1)%20deliver%20solid%20sound%2C%20but%20they%20favor%20a%20balanced%20profile%20over%20vibrancy.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Hayes%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStylish%20headphones%20with%20no%20brains%20would%20be%20disappointing.%20Luckily%2C%20the%20Headphone%20(1)%20sound%20good%2C%20providing%20ample%20substance%20to%20go%20with%20their%20flashy%20style.%20The%20headphones'%20acoustics%20have%20actually%20been%20developed%20in%20partnership%20with%20KEF%2C%20a%20company%20known%20for%20high-end%20audio%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resulting%20sound%20profile%20is%20neutral%20and%20pleasing%2C%20but%20does%20lack%20some%20personality.%20They%20aren't%20as%20vibrant%20as%20headphones%20from%20Bose%20or%20Sony%2C%20but%20they%20still%20sound%20full.%20I%20never%20felt%20let%20down%20by%20songs%20with%20heavy%20synths%2C%20those%20pounding%20the%20kick%20drum%2C%20or%20ones%20with%20thick%20bass%20lines.%20Importantly%2C%20the%20headphones%20also%20have%20great%20clarity%20throughout%20the%20midrange.%20Vocals%20were%20present%20and%20detailed%2C%20while%20instruments%20like%20guitars%20were%20audible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20talk%20of%20the%20sound%20is%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20default%20experience%20with%20tuning%20left%20as%20is%20out%20of%20the%20box.%20But%20using%20the%20Nothing%20X%20app%2C%20you%20can%20heavily%20tweak%20the%20sound%20via%20simplified%20or%20advanced%20EQ%20settings.%20I'm%20not%20against%20adjusting%20a%20headphone's%20EQ%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20you%20should%20need%20to%2C%20so%20it's%20great%20that%20the%20Headphone%20(1)%20perform%20well%20without%20any%20tinkering.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20bass%20enhancement%20toggle%20to%20boost%20the%20low-end%20for%20people%20who%20crave%20a%20bit%20more%20oomph.%20This%20control%20is%20also%20in%20the%20Nothing%20X%20app%20and%20doesn't%20require%20knowledge%20of%20frequency%20bands%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20support%20for%20a%20spatial%20audio%20mode%2C%20which%20can%20transform%20ster